    "gettingAround": "Temagami village is small and walkable. The station, the canoe outfitters, the local restaurants, and Bear Island ferry are all accessible without a car. For backcountry access you need either a canoe or a water taxi. This is genuinely a place where your own two feet and a paddle are the primary modes of transport.",
