    "heroTagline": "End of the line, gateway to polar bear country and James Bay",
    "editorialIntro": "Cochrane is where the Northlander ends and the true north begins. This small town of 5,000 people sits at the junction of two railway lines and three great watersheds, a geographical pivot point where the waters flow north toward Hudson Bay. Getting off the train here feels genuinely different. The air is different. The sky is bigger. The boreal forest presses closer.\n\nThe Cochrane Polar Bear Habitat is the centrepiece attraction and it is remarkable. The resident polar bears can be observed at close range in a natural-feeling habitat. There is nowhere else in the world where you can arrive by train, walk to a polar bear facility, and watch these extraordinary animals go about their day.\n\nFrom Cochrane you can also board the Polar Bear Express, the legendary train to Moosonee on the shore of James Bay. This is one of the great rail journeys remaining in Canada, 300 kilometres through pure boreal wilderness to a community accessible only by plane, train, or winter ice road.",
