    "pageTitle": "Things to Do in Temiskaming Shores by Train | Northlander Guide",
    "metaDescription": "Your complete guide to Temiskaming Shores on the Northlander route. Devil's Rock, Lake Timiskaming, a stunning farmers market, and the heart of the Clay Belt.",
    "heroTagline": "Dramatic cliffs, fertile farmland, and the surprise of the north",
    "editorialIntro": "Temiskaming Shores surprises people. They expect a small Northern Ontario service town and they find instead a city of genuine character sitting on the shore of one of the most dramatic lakes in Ontario. Lake Timiskaming is not a typical Ontario lake. It is deep, narrow, and geologically ancient, bounded on both sides by cliffs and hills that give it the feel of a Norwegian fjord transported to Northern Ontario.\n\nThe city encompasses three former communities, New Liskeard, Haileybury, and Dymond Township, each with its own character. New Liskeard has the most active commercial downtown with a farmers market that is genuinely one of the best in Northern Ontario. Haileybury has the waterfront and the remarkable Devil's Rock, a 300-foot cliff that drops straight into the lake and offers one of the most dramatic viewpoints in Ontario.\n\nThe agricultural heritage of the Clay Belt begins here. The flat, fertile land north and west of Temiskaming Shores was formed by a post-glacial lake and supports farming that would surprise anyone who thinks Northern Ontario is all rock and forest. The farms here produce real food and the local food culture reflects it.",
