    "pageTitle": "Things to Do in Bracebridge by Train | Northlander Guide",
    "metaDescription": "Your complete guide to Bracebridge on the Northlander route. Waterfalls, galleries, great food, and the heart of Muskoka.",
    "heroTagline": "The waterfall town at the heart of Muskoka",
    "editorialIntro": "Bracebridge announces itself with a waterfall. Bracebridge Falls drops through the centre of town and the sound of it greets you before you even see it, a rushing, constant reminder that this is a town built on water and shaped by it. The Muskoka River winds through and around Bracebridge creating a landscape of bridges, mills, and riverfront parks that gives the town a particular character unlike anywhere else in Muskoka.\n\nManitoba Street is the main commercial artery and it is one of the best small-town shopping streets in Ontario. Independent boutiques, art galleries, bookshops, and restaurants occupy the heritage storefronts in a way that feels organic rather than curated. The Muskoka Arts and Crafts summer show draws artisans from across the region and is genuinely one of the better craft shows in the province.\n\nBracebridge is also the seat of Muskoka District government which gives it a year-round population and an economy that does not entirely depend on summer tourism. That means the restaurants stay open, the coffee shops are excellent, and there is an authentic community life that you can feel when you walk the streets even in the shoulder seasons.",
    "gettingHere": "The Bracebridge station shelter is at 85 Hiram Street. The town centre and Manitoba Street are about 10 minutes walk from the station. Taxis are available. The station has some parking. The walk into town passes through a pleasant residential neighbourhood and crosses the river.",
    "gettingAround": "Bracebridge is walkable once you reach the town centre. The station at 85 Hiram Street is about 10 minutes walk from Manitoba Street, the main commercial strip. The falls are easy to reach on foot. Cycling is excellent along the river trails. Taxis are available for longer distances.",
    "springHighlights": "Spring runoff makes Bracebridge Falls spectacular. The river runs high and fast and the sound carries through the whole town. Fishing season opens and the river is excellent for trout.",
    "summerHighlights": "Summer brings Bracebridge to life with festivals, the arts and crafts show, and the full Muskoka experience. The river is perfect for paddling. Book restaurants on summer weekends.",
