    "heroTagline": "Canada's grandest railway hall, where every journey north begins",
    "editorialIntro": "There is no better place to begin a train adventure than Toronto Union Station. Built in the Beaux-Arts style and completed in 1927, this is one of the most beautiful buildings in Canada and the busiest transit hub in the country. The Great Hall alone is worth arriving early for, a soaring limestone cathedral of travel with its arched windows and marble floors that have welcomed millions of passengers over nearly a century.\n\nUnion Station sits at the heart of downtown Toronto, steps from the waterfront, the CN Tower, the Rogers Centre, and the Distillery District. Whether you have an hour to kill before your train or a full day to explore, the area around Union is genuinely one of the most interesting urban environments in the country. The underground PATH network connects you to hundreds of shops and restaurants without ever going outside, which matters a great deal in January.\n\nThis is also where your relationship with the Northlander begins. Stand on the platform as the train arrives and feel the particular anticipation of a long journey by rail. By the time you reach Cochrane eleven hours later, you will understand why people who ride trains once tend to ride them for the rest of their lives.",
