    "gettingAround": "Union Station is arguably the most connected point in Canada. TTC subway, GO Transit, VIA Rail, the UP Express, and dozens of bus routes all converge here. Once in the station neighbourhood, the PATH underground walkway connects to over 70 city blocks of shops, food, and services without going outside. Taxis and rideshare are available at multiple exits. Bixi bike share stations are throughout the area.",
    "springHighlights": "Spring transforms the waterfront just south of Union into one of the most pleasant urban walks in Toronto. The cherry blossoms along the Harbourfront arrive in late April. The Martin Goodman Trail opens up for cycling and walking along Lake Ontario. Patio season begins in earnest and the restaurants around the station throw open their doors.",
    "summerHighlights": "Summer at Union Station is electric. Blue Jays games at Rogers Centre draw huge crowds to the neighbourhood. The harbourfront festivals run almost every weekend. The CN Tower observation deck has its longest lines but also its clearest views. The restaurants on King Street West reach their peak energy.",
    "fallHighlights": "Fall is genuinely the best time to be in downtown Toronto. The humidity breaks, the light turns golden, and the city feels purposeful. TIFF, the Toronto International Film Festival, takes over the Entertainment District in September. The patios stay open well into October. The waterfront walk is spectacular in fall colours.",
